verbose_text: 15 Moreover, Li et al. 16 reported that exogenous H 2 S contributed to recovery of ischemic post-conditioning-induced cardioprotection by reducing the reactive oxygen species level through downregulation of NF-kappaB and JAK2-STAT3 signaling pathways in aging cardiomyocytes; this indicated that hydrogen therapy may improve AKI via JAK2 / STAT3 signaling.
